column52:
Amber Heard does not represent me as a woman.

We're women and the majority of Johnnys supporters are female survivours themselves. This is a message from all of us to Amber, her legal team, her supporters and the mainstream media;

You will not change our mind. Not by gaslighting us, not by calling us misogynistic, not by implying that we're stupid for believing a man and NOT by calling us traitors. You'reÂ doing all of this in the name of feminism, in the name of all women, in the name of metoo. All of this while you belittle the women who doesn't share your narrative, the women who's sided with Johnny. How is that feminism? How is it feminism to talk about all of the women who believe him, as if we're not capable of thinking independantly and make up our own minds about things? As if we're just being manipulated by men?We are strong, intelligent and independant women, we have seen and listened to all of the evidence available and we believe Johnny.Â How is it feminism to leave all male victims behind?

You're obsessed with shaming and tearing down women you don't agree with.Â But you will not shame us into disbelief, you will not shame us into silence.Â

Instead she should focus on her child and on getting serious help with her addictions and her mental health issues

column2: I survived Domestic Abuse with my disabled child. I had to move states, we were stalked with Private Investigators. The day I moved to my daughters college town in another state, my abuser rode right by my new residence. We were not safe until he died. Ambers own words proved who was the abuser, I heard my abuser in her own recordings. I have been triggered by this trial, my child has been triggered by the words spoken by Amber in this trial. We are now being gaslighted by the media, Drs, professors, Eve Barlow etc. We are being called stupid, Depp fans, mysoginists, enablers etc. I spoke in front of Senate to promote tougher laws for DV and SV to be called these names by the protectors of an abuser, Amber Heard.  The current ignorance thrown at us as Survivors is abuse, it must stop!

column52:
Amber Heard does not represent me as a woman.

We're women and the majority of Johnnys supporters are female survivours themselves. This is a message from all of us to Amber, her legal team, her supporters and the mainstream media;

You will not change our mind. Not by gaslighting us, not by calling us misogynistic, not by implying that we're stupid for believing a man and NOT by calling us traitors. You'reÂ doing all of this in the name of feminism, in the name of all women, in the name of metoo. All of this while you belittle the women who doesn't share your narrative, the women who's sided with Johnny. How is that feminism? How is it feminism to talk about all of the women who believe him, as if we're not capable of thinking independantly and make up our own minds about things? As if we're just being manipulated by men?We are strong, intelligent and independant women, we have seen and listened to all of the evidence available and we believe Johnny.Â How is it feminism to leave all male victims behind?

You're obsessed with shaming and tearing down women you don't agree with.Â But you will not shame us into disbelief, you will not shame us into silence.Â

We're women and the majority of Johnnys supporters are female survivours themselves. This is a message from all of us to Amber, her legal team, her supporters and the mainstream media;

You will not change our mind. Not by gaslighting us, not by calling us misogynistic, not by implying that we're stupid for believing a man and NOT by calling us traitors. You'reÂ doing all of this in the name of feminism, in the name of all women, in the name of metoo. All of this while you belittle the women who doesn't share your narrative, the women who's sided with Johnny. How is that feminism? How is it feminism to talk about all of the women who believe him, as if we're not capable of thinking independantly and make up our own minds about things? As if we're just being manipulated by men?We are strong, intelligent and independant women, we have seen and listened to all of the evidence available and we believe Johnny.Â How is it feminism to leave all male victims behind?

You're obsessed with shaming and tearing down women you don't agree with.Â But you will not shame us into disbelief, you will not shame us into silence.Â

column2:
I'm a survivor of domestic abuse. I'm a woman. I was never a fan of Johnny Depp! I AM a fan of the TRUTH! I watched the entire trial. I saw/heard ALL the evidence including the stuff that didn't make it in. 
Amber does NOT & NEVER will be a spokesperson for me! Neither will Elaine Bredehoft! Amber is an abusive woman who has abused an ex wife, friends, her husband, employees, and her own sister. 

Mainstream media wants to paint us as misogynistic or just super Depp fans and that's just false! The Mainstream media doesn't speak for us and as long as they're defending Amber they're complicit in HARMING victims/survivors further! 
The Mainstream media afforded my now ex husband the same type of support when he murdered & raped a girl & killed her family! THE MEDIA decided to blame it on the Iraq war being just hard and stressful. They decided to try to get me to talk, even offering a couple hundred thousand dollars to get an interview where I'd day the war stressed him out and he had no leadership instead of me saying he is and has been an abusive monster and the army failed me and the family he hurt. And the courts failed us as well, and the army failed by still sending him while knowing what he was capable of! Mainstream didn't want me to say all that. They wanted lies. They protect abusers and always have. They spin narratives and always have. 
Amber is being protected. She and her attorney are liars. Amber does NOT represent me and the only abuse survivors she does represent are the ones being manipulated & gaslit by her. 

We are abuse survivors. We are strong. We are women. And we are not represented by amber heard .  We are not misogynistic. We are not all far right wing extremists. We are from all different backgrounds. All religions. All have different political views. And Our support for Johnny Depp, the ACTUAL survivor of domestic abuse, has actually let us all come together and agree on this issue- Amber heard lied, still lies, as does her attorney, and we all support the truth. We don't want or need Amber heard to say anything on our behalf. Ever! 
We stand together against abusers and together as survivors and with victims! We speak for us! We realize men, too, can be and are abused by women! 
I did not almost die at the hands of my ex husband so that Amber freaking Heard could prance around and act like she's telling our story. Her story is one of abuse, except she is the perpetrator of such abuse! Not the victim or survivor! 
She does not speak for me .
